en_717820_0	Intending to educate the 61 Division troops on the incidence of suicide and the importance of maintaining balanced mental health, a lecture session, organized on a proposal of Brigadier K.D.C.G.J Thilakarathna, General Officer Commanding (GOC), 61 Division with the support of Major General Kumudu Perera, Commander, Security Forces - Wanni (SF-W) got underway at the 61 Division Headquarters on Tuesday (16) in Vavuniya.
en_717820_1	25 Officers including 611 Brigade Commander, three hundred plus troops attended these lectures, conducted by lecturers of the Directorate of Preventive Medicine and Mental Health of the Sri Lanka Army, led by Dr Nishyanka Gunarathna, the visiting lecturer at Peradeniya University.
en_717820_2	Several psychiatric counsellors took part in the programme.
